The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Saturday, January 13, 2007

 Troop showcase

 Know Your Army exhibition will open at Fort William Driving Range, 10 am. Entry for public through HRBC gate on Strand Road. 

 Physics amp; wildlife

 Nobel laureate Sir Anthony Leggett will speak on Does the Everyday World Really Obey Quantum Mechanics, at GD Birla Sabhagar, 6.45 pm.

 Fourth Aranyak Wildlife Film Festival at Nandan. Today: Seminar on wildlife crime in India, 1 pm; Elephant Death by Trains in North Bengal, a slide show, 3 pm; The Great Indian Tiger Crisis, 6 pm.

 Eye on art amp; soiree

 CIMA Annual 2006, an exhibition of artworks, at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.

 Travelling on a personal journey, works by Iris Hudson Ghosh, will open at Galerie 88, 3 pm to 7 pm.

 Srijaner Srijitora, a show of paintings by children, at Academy of Fine Arts, South Gallery, 2 pm to 8 pm.

 Annual musical soiree at the courtyard of Laha Bati, 5.30 pm onwards.




